    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>PARENTAL NOTICE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Abhi Raghunathan</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Raghunathan, Abhi</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>New Jersey Assembly, after state Supreme Court rules bill requiring parental notification before minors can obtain abortions is unconstitutional, holds public hearing on constitutional amendment that would require parent to receive notice before children undergo any medical or surgical procedure or treatment (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>In a new approach to requiring parental notification before minors get an abotion, the State Assembly held a public hearing last week on a constitutional amendment that would require parents to receive notice before their children undergo any medical or surgical procedure or treatment. The New Jersey Supreme Court ruled in August that a bill requiring parental notification before minors could obtain an abortion was unconstitutional. The amendment must receive either a three-fifths majority in both houses of the Legislature in one year or a simple majority in both houses in two consecutive years and then be ratified in a public ballot.</p>
        <p>Abhi Raghunathan</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
